[1
Date: Sat, 22 Jan 2000 12:41:01 +0600
From: Nick Honhold <nick@plewland.demon.co.uk>

I think all of us who have worked in the 'Third World" have been frustrated
over the unwillingness of many countries to admit to any medical problem
with international implications.
[SNIP
The Third World truly is a different world, and it is necessary to
differentiate the desirable from the feasible. A small point this, but I
think it is unfair and incorrect to talk as if it is only "third world"
countries that are selective in their disease reporting. Would that it were
so.
--
